/*
=========================================
React Router Concepts Used
=========================================

1. Dynamic Route Params (:id)
   - The route contains a variable parameter.
   - Example: /student/1
   - Here, 1 is the dynamic id.

2. useParams()
   - Reads the id value from the URL.
   - Allows us to identify which student's details to display.

3. Link Component
   - Creates clickable navigation between pages.
   - Prevents full page refresh and provides SPA navigation.

4. Lifting State Up
   - Student data is stored in a common parent component.
   - Data is passed to different pages through props.
   - Ensures all pages access the same state.

5. Array.find()
   - Used to locate a specific student object.
   - Matches the URL id with the student id.
   - Returns the selected student's details for display.

=========================================
*/
